Besides, the structure and morphology stability of PhE2-ITA-Glu FGNs also played very significant roles in their bioapplications. Therefore, the AIE dye leakage study was firstly carried out to test their structure stability by dialysis against PBS solution (pH 7.4) or THF for three days using 7000 Da Mw cut-off dialysis membranes. The results revealed that there was no dye leakage, which was attributed to the covalent connection of PhE2 with the glycopolymer. To further investigate the morphology stability of PhE2-ITA-Glu FGNs in water, the critical micelle concentration (CMC) was tested by determining the fluorescence intensity of PhE2-ITA-Glu in PBS solution (pH 7.4) at 580 nm versus the logarithm of their concentration. Thanks to the cross-linked structure of PhE2-ITA-Glu, the CMC was calculated as low as 0.0018 mg mL−1 (Fig. 5
                        ). At the concentration below CMC, the detected emission intensity was very low since the AIE monomer was not in the aggregated state. However, when the concentration of PhE2-ITA-Glu reached above CMC, the aggregated emission increased abruptly. Therefore, the obtained PhE2-ITA-Glu FGNs would demonstrate great stability in both morphology and structure when the concentration of PhE2-ITA-Glu in aqueous solution above CMC.
